If you or your ex-spouse are one of those sceptics, arguing that it is just another money-making gimmick, take a moment to read and reflect on these notes.On father's day, we have the opportunity for an annual show of honour and appreciation for fathers &ndash; not only your own father but also the father of your children. Being divorced does not relieve you of the responsibility to teach your children the importance of special occasions. Instead, it is also a chance to teach your children to consider the relationships they have with the men in their lives.As the mother, your ex-spouse (the father of your children) probably relies on you to initiate celebrations. Don't try to punish him and your children, by deliberately spoiling the day. Instead, here are some valuable tips on what you could do to make it count:Honour your children's father &ndash; let him have a wonderful father's day!